sentences: In 2006, he graduated from Full Sail University where he studied audio engineering.
In 2010, J Beatzz received his first placement contributing to Big Boi of Outkast solo hit album, Sir Luscious Left Foot, producing the record "General Patton".
The record was featured and revamped during the NFL Playoffs in 2011.
Astroworld was nominated for Best Rap Album at the 2019 Grammy Awards.
In 2018, he produced the tracks "Coco Chanel" and "Inspirations Outro" both featured on Nicki Minaj fourth studio album Queen.
On January 11, 2019 the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) announced the Queen as certified platinum.
Joshua Adams (born April 13), professionally known as J Beatzz, is an American Grammy Award nominated, platinum selling, hip hop record producer.
